### Storage vs Memory
- Use `memory` for temporary data
- Use `storage` only when necessary
- Cache storage variables in memory

### Loop Optimization
- Cache array length outside loops
- Use `++i` instead of `i++`
- Avoid expensive operations in loops

### Data Types
- Use `uint256` over smaller uints (cheaper)
- Pack variables to save storage slots
- Use `bytes32` instead of `string` when possible

### Functions
- Mark view/pure functions correctly
- Use external over public when possible
- Batch operations to save gas

### Examples
